cmPerformanceMIB.description: This module defines the Performance Monitoring MIB definitions used by the F3 (FSP150CM/CC) product lines. Copyright (C) ADVA Optical Networking.

cmEthernetAccPortStatsTable.name: cmEthernetAccPortStatsTable
cmEthernetAccPortStatsTable.description: A collection of Ethernet Access Port related statistics. These reflect the current data.

cmEthernetAccPortStatsEntry.name: cmEthernetAccPortStatsEntry
cmEthernetAccPortStatsEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmEthernetAccPortStatsTable. Entries exist in this table for each Ethernet interface/port.

cmEthernetAccPortStatsIndex.name: cmEthernetAccPortStatsIndex
cmEthernetAccPortStatsIndex.description: An arbitrary integer index value used to uniquely identify this Ethernet Access Port statistics entry. 1 - 15min 2 - 1day 3 - rollover 4 - 5min

cmEthernetAccPortStatsIntervalType.name: cmEthernetAccPortStatsIntervalType
cmEthernetAccPortStatsIntervalType.description: Interval over which Performance Monitoring data is collected.

cmEthernetAccPortStatsValid.name: cmEthernetAccPortStatsValid
cmEthernetAccPortStatsValid.description: Indicates the validity of the bin.

cmEthernetAccPortStatsAction.name: cmEthernetAccPortStatsAction
cmEthernetAccPortStatsAction.description: Allows the Manager to clear the bin.

cmEthernetAccPortThresholdInterval.description: The interval over which monitored value is sampled and compared with the specified threshold.

cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVariable.name: cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVariable
cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVariable.description: The object identifier of the particular variable to be sampled.

cmEthernetAccPortThresholdValueLo.name: cmEthernetAccPortThresholdValueLo
cmEthernetAccPortThresholdValueLo.description: Lower 32 bits of the threshold value. Please note that in case of cmEthernetAccPortStatsOPR, cmEthernetAccPortStatsOPT and cmEthernetAccPortStatsTEMP, the values are 2's complement, since these could have negative values.

cmEthernetAccPortThresholdValueHi.name: cmEthernetAccPortThresholdValueHi
cmEthernetAccPortThresholdValueHi.description: Higher 32 bits of the threshold value. Please note that in case of cmEthernetAccPortStatsOPR, cmEthernetAccPortStatsOPT and cmEthernetAccPortStatsTEMP, the values are 2's complement, since these could have negative values.

cmEthernetAccPortThresholdMonValue.name: cmEthernetAccPortThresholdMonValue
cmEthernetAccPortThresholdMonValue.description: Monitored value corresponding to cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVariable. Please note that in case of cmEthernetAccPortStatsOPR, cmEthernetAccPortStatsOPT and cmEthernetAccPortStatsTEMP, the values are 2's complement, since these could be negative values.

cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVarTable.name: cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVarTable
cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVarTable.description: A table of entries that allow manageability of Ethernet Access Port Threshold variances.

cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVarEntry.name: cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVarEntry
cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVarEntry.description: A conceptual row in the cmEthernetAccPortThresholdTable.

cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVarOprVariance.name: cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVarOprVariance
cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVarOprVariance.description: Variance in the Optical Power received (in dbM), beyond which threshold crossing alert will be generated.

cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVarOptVariance.name: cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVarOptVariance
cmEthernetAccPortThresholdVarOptVariance.description: Variance in the Optical Power transmitted (in dbM), beyond which threshold crossing alert will be generated.
